-- Tier 3 — ADDITIONAL fully-attributed Varicella Investigation (R3-F)
-- =====================================================================
-- Goal: raise dbo.var_datamart column coverage (210/231) by authoring a
-- BRAND-NEW, fully-attributed Varicella investigation that populates the
-- ~21 columns the existing baseline var_datamart row leaves NULL.
--
-- PURELY ADDITIVE. Every row this fixture writes is keyed in agent R3-F's
-- reserved UID block 22028400-22028999. NOTHING shared / foundation is
-- mutated:
--   * The shared Varicella PHC 22002000 is NOT referenced or re-EXEC'd
--     (the quarantined zz_var_datamart_enrich_r3.sql regressed var_datamart
--     2->0 precisely by re-running sp_nrt_investigation_postprocessing +
--     sp_f_var_pam_postprocessing + sp_var_datamart_postprocessing on the
--     SHARED 22002000, churning the shared fact/dim rows. We do NOT repeat
--     that — this fixture builds its own PHC and only EXECs the chain on it.)
--   * Foundation D_PATIENT key 3 / patient 20000000, the shared USER_PROFILE,
--     F_VAR_PAM existing rows — all untouched. We author our OWN D_PATIENT,
--     D_PROVIDER(s), D_ORGANIZATION(s), USER_PROFILE, EVENT_METRIC,
--     NOTIFICATION/NOTIFICATION_EVENT rows in our UID block so the NEW
--     var_datamart row resolves every attribution column to OUR new dims.
--
-- WHY DIRECT RDB_MODERN DIM INSERTS (not just ODSE + SP chain)
--   F_VAR_PAM resolves PERSON_KEY / PROVIDER_KEY / PHYSICIAN_KEY /
--   PERSON_AS_REPORTER_KEY / ORG_AS_REPORTER_KEY / HOSPITAL_KEY by reading
--   nrt_investigation's investigator_id / physician_id / person_as_reporter_uid
--   / org_as_reporter_uid / hospital_uid / patient_id columns and joining
--   D_PROVIDER.PROVIDER_UID / D_ORGANIZATION.ORGANIZATION_UID /
--   D_PATIENT.PATIENT_UID (240 SP lines 64-114, 144-328). var_datamart then
--   joins those keys back to the dims to surface the names/SSN/comments
--   (250 SP #PATIENT/#PROVIDER/#PHYSICIAN/#REPORTER/#ORG_REPORTER/#HOSPITAL
--   tables, lines 154-372). So the *_UID columns on our nrt_investigation row
--   must point at OUR new dims, and the dims must carry the demographic /
--   name fields. We author them directly in RDB_MODERN — the project's
--   established additive pattern for dims with no per-row event SP partner.
--
-- TARGET COLUMNS THE BASELINE ROW LACKS, FILLED BY THE NEW ROW
--   Patient demographics (D_PATIENT, our patient 22028410):
--     PATIENT_SSN, PATIENT_NAME_SUFFIX, PATIENT_GENERAL_COMMENTS,
--     PATIENT_PHONE_EXT_HOME, PATIENT_PHONE_EXT_WORK
--     (+ RACE_CALCULATED, RACE_CALC_DETAILS already on baseline but
--      re-populated here for the new row).
--   Investigator (D_PROVIDER 22028420 via investigator_id):
--     INVESTIGATOR_FIRST_NAME, INVESTIGATOR_LAST_NAME, INVESTIGATOR_PHONE_NUMBER
--   Physician (D_PROVIDER 22028421 via physician_id):
--     PHYSICIAN_FIRST_NAME, PHYSICIAN_LAST_NAME, PHYSICIAN_PHONE_NUMBER
--   Reporter (D_PROVIDER 22028422 via person_as_reporter_uid):
--     REPORTER_FIRST_NAME, REPORTER_LAST_NAME, REPORTER_PHONE_NUMBER
--   Reporting source (D_ORGANIZATION 22028430 via org_as_reporter_uid):
--     REPORTING_SOURCE_NAME
--   Hospital (D_ORGANIZATION 22028431 via hospital_uid):
--     HOSPITAL_NAME
--   User attribution (USER_PROFILE nedss_entry_id 22028440 + EVENT_METRIC
--   EVENT_UID=our PHC + NOTIFICATION submitted_by):
--     INVESTIGATION_CREATED_BY, INVESTIGATION_LAST_UPDTD_BY,
--     NOTIFICATION_SUBMITTER  (also NOTIFICATION_STATUS / NOTIFICATION_SENT_DATE)
--   Multi-value confirmation method (3 nrt_investigation_confirmation rows):
--     CONFIRMATION_METHOD_1, CONFIRMATION_METHOD_2, CONFIRMATION_METHOD_3,
--     CONFIRMATION_METHOD_ALL  (codes LD/CD/E grounded in NBS_SRTE PHC_CONF_M,
--     verified live 2026-06-02; descs are >2 chars so the 250 SP LEN()>2
--     gate at lines 1038-1040 slots COL2/COL3).
--
-- VERIFICATION CALL-CHAIN (tail-EXECs at bottom), all on OUR PHC 22028400:
--   sp_nrt_investigation_postprocessing  @id_list=22028400
--       nrt_investigation -> INVESTIGATION; rebuilds confirmation_method +
--       confirmation_method_group from our nrt_investigation_confirmation
--       rows (005 SP lines 709-858) for OUR investigation_key only.
--   sp_nrt_d_var_pam_postprocessing       @phc_uids=22028400     -> D_VAR_PAM
--   sp_nrt_d_rash_loc_gen_postprocessing  @phc_uids=22028400     -> D_RASH_LOC_GEN
--   sp_nrt_d_pcr_source_postprocessing    @phc_id_list=22028400  -> D_PCR_SOURCE
--   sp_nrt_var_pam_ldf_postprocessing     @phc_uids=22028400     -> VAR_PAM_LDF
--   sp_f_var_pam_postprocessing           @phc_id_list=22028400  -> F_VAR_PAM
--   sp_var_datamart_postprocessing        @phc_uids=22028400     -> VAR_DATAMART
--   (We DO tail-EXEC f_var_pam + var_datamart here, scoped to OUR new PHC,
--    because the orchestrator Step-9 PHC_UIDS list does not include 22028400.
--    These EXECs only INSERT a NEW fact/datamart row keyed to our PHC; they
